 mouse.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You don&#039;t react to the insignificant impact, but she lets out a gasp.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;ARE YOU HURT?  SORRY!&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;I&#039;m fine, it barely hit me.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;She hugs you close, gently running plastic claws through your hair.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;SORRY.  SORRY.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;She eventually releases you.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;What do you say we explore?  We could look for more peripherals and maybe a generator.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;ALRIGHT.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The two of you set off again, her claws again tapping to a different rhythm than her heart rate.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;...something about that monitor&#039;s beeping unnerves you...</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You peek into a ruined office.  A briefcase sits atop a splintered desk.  You walk in, with Kitten following.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The desk bears a small plastic plaque reading &quot;ASSISTANT RESEARCHER RICHARD&quot;.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;A low-fi growling rumbles from your companion&#039;s terminal as she attempts to snap the plaque in half with her bare hands...</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;To no avail. She simply isn&#039;t strong enough...</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Kitten sighs and drops the plaque, gently laying a hand over her racing heart monitor.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;SHOULDN&#039;T LET MYSELF GET SO UPSET.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;...a faint, shuddering breath punctuates her sentence.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&g